# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — organized by artifact class, most-specific first.
#
# Ground rules:
#   - Patterns are root-anchored (leading /) wherever the artifact only ever
#     appears at one path; unanchored patterns are reserved for cruft that
#     can appear anywhere (editor swap, OS metadata, __pycache__).
#   - Lockfiles and toolchain pins are COMMITTED, never ignored: go.sum,
#     uv.lock, .python-version, .golangci.yml, .goreleaser.yaml.
#   - Generated protobuf code (pkg/*/proto/v1/) is deliberately committed —
#     CI fails on drift — so nothing under pkg/ is ignored.
# =============================================================================

# --- Go: build outputs -------------------------------------------------------
# Every compiled artifact goes to bin/ (repo rule: no exceptions, including
# scratch binaries and `go test -c` output). dist/ belongs to GoReleaser only.
/bin/
/dist/

# Compiled binaries that would appear if the bin/-only rule is fat-fingered —
# ignored so an accident never lands in a commit.
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
*.test
__debug_bin*

# --- Go: test, coverage & profiling artifacts --------------------------------
*.out
coverage.txt
coverage.html
coverage.xml
*.cover
*.prof
*.pprof

# --- Go: workspace files -----------------------------------------------------
# Local multi-module workspaces are a per-developer convenience, never shared.
go.work
go.work.sum

# --- Docs site (MkDocs Material) ---------------------------------------------
# Built site, the uv-managed Python env, and plugin caches (social cards
# render into .cache/plugin/). The toolchain itself is committed:
# pyproject.toml, uv.lock, .python-version, mkdocs.yml, overrides/.
/site/
/.venv/
/.cache/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]

# --- Secrets & local environment --------------------------------------------
# configuration.md's env() model means real secret values live in the
# operator's shell env or an untracked .env file, never in agent.hcl or
# this repo. .envrc (direnv) routinely exports credentials — same policy.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
.envrc

# --- Claude Code local/ephemeral state ---------------------------------------
# settings.json (shared) and .claude/rules/*.md (project instructions) are
# checked in; per-machine state is not.
/.claude/settings.local.json
/.claude/worktrees/

# --- Logs & scratch ----------------------------------------------------------
*.log
*.tmp
/tmp/

# --- Editors / IDEs ----------------------------------------------------------
# JetBrains (GoLand et al.) and VS Code ignored wholesale rather than the
# sprawling per-plugin allowlist gitignore.io generates; nobody here needs
# shared run configurations or code styles committed.
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# --- OS cruft ----------------------------------------------------------------
# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
.fseventsd
.DocumentRevisions-V100
*.icloud

# Linux
.directory
.Trash-*
.fuse_hidden*
.nfs*

# Windows
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/
*.lnk
